{
  "doc_id": "30611",
  "text": "Epidermal growth factor receptor (EGFR) is a receptor tyrosine kinase, a member of the ErbB-family and a regulator of various cellular processes, including cell survival, differentiation, migration and cell growth [CITATION_1] . The EGFR is implicated in pathological processes, such as oncogenesis, and is linked with a poor prognosis in several epithelial carcinomas [CITATION_2] . Inhibition of uncontrolled EGFR expression improved treatment of malignant diseases, such as breast and lung cancers [CITATION_3] . The investigation of EGFR and its signaling pathway is, therefore, important in research concerning the tumor biology of this entity.",
